00:02:57.375 --> 00:02:59.775
IT 2030 This is our topic

00:03:01.135 --> 00:03:04.895
CIOs and technology leaders worldwide are

00:03:04.895 --> 00:03:05.855
all wondering

00:03:06.735 --> 00:03:09.295
more than delivering AI for business

00:03:09.375 --> 00:03:12.815
should they be reinventing IT itself for

00:03:12.815 --> 00:03:13.695
the AI age

00:03:14.895 --> 00:03:17.295
Some of you are already working on a plan

00:03:18.204 --> 00:03:20.764
Some of you are considering and some of

00:03:20.764 --> 00:03:22.044
you are asked by the board

00:03:22.844 --> 00:03:25.164
To address this me and a few of my

00:03:25.164 --> 00:03:27.324
colleagues started putting together

00:03:27.324 --> 00:03:29.324
research at the end of last year

00:03:30.204 --> 00:03:32.844
and since the time we have taken feedback

00:03:32.844 --> 00:03:35.084
from many of you who have been gracious

00:03:35.084 --> 00:03:37.724
with your input to shape this presentation

00:03:38.684 --> 00:03:39.484
Let's jump right in

00:03:44.232 --> 00:03:44.552
So

00:03:45.352 --> 00:03:49.023
as we all know AI is a powerful force And

00:03:49.023 --> 00:03:51.663
I think we can all agree that while there

00:03:51.663 --> 00:03:54.303
are many different forces that can impact

00:03:54.303 --> 00:03:59.183
IT and here are some geopolitics economic

00:03:59.183 --> 00:04:02.383
activity and so there could be others that

00:04:02.383 --> 00:04:05.823
impact IT I think we can all agree AI is

00:04:05.903 --> 00:04:08.383
the fundamental powerful force that is

00:04:08.383 --> 00:04:09.343
going to reshape IT

00:04:11.044 --> 00:04:13.684
And when we talk to many of you we see

00:04:13.684 --> 00:04:16.164
that there are three big areas why this

00:04:16.164 --> 00:04:17.284
question becomes important

00:04:18.644 --> 00:04:21.364
One is AIdriven efficiencies

00:04:22.724 --> 00:04:26.164
We can all see that because of AI the

00:04:26.164 --> 00:04:28.324
ability to build technology is getting

00:04:28.324 --> 00:04:28.724
easier

00:04:29.604 --> 00:04:32.164
It might not be as much as some people in

00:04:32.164 --> 00:04:34.884
the media or in the tech industries

00:04:34.884 --> 00:04:35.764
portrayed to be

00:04:36.648 --> 00:04:37.688
But there is benefit

00:04:38.648 --> 00:04:41.288
whether it's in building code or managing

00:04:41.368 --> 00:04:41.768
IT

00:04:43.048 --> 00:04:45.768
So based on that will the IT organization

00:04:45.768 --> 00:04:48.488
in the future be smaller or bigger

00:04:49.848 --> 00:04:50.248
Second

00:04:51.208 --> 00:04:53.688
we all see increased interest from

00:04:53.768 --> 00:04:55.848
business wanting to build their own

00:04:55.848 --> 00:04:56.408
technology

00:04:57.288 --> 00:04:58.648
We call it democratization

00:04:59.737 --> 00:05:02.137
This used to have a negative connotation a

00:05:02.137 --> 00:05:03.017
few years ago

00:05:03.897 --> 00:05:06.777
with shadow IT I'm sure most of you are

00:05:06.777 --> 00:05:09.817
familiar with shadow IT When the worry was

00:05:09.977 --> 00:05:12.697
rampant technology use that is done

00:05:12.697 --> 00:05:14.937
without guardrails in business ends up

00:05:15.017 --> 00:05:15.737
impacting IT

00:05:16.581 --> 00:05:19.861
But now democratization is on a forward

00:05:19.861 --> 00:05:23.381
march No code agent builders wipe coding

00:05:23.941 --> 00:05:26.261
These type of tools are enabling business

00:05:26.341 --> 00:05:26.741
to build more

00:05:28.021 --> 00:05:29.141
And the third one is

00:05:30.128 --> 00:05:33.088
Because of the ability to use AI directly

00:05:33.968 --> 00:05:37.488
or use AI to build code we have a new

00:05:37.488 --> 00:05:41.155
question Should I increase my build mix

00:05:41.155 --> 00:05:42.835
versus buy compared to before

00:05:43.955 --> 00:05:47.075
I'll give an example A few months ago

00:05:47.875 --> 00:05:50.675
a CIO of a large global bank asked me

00:05:51.235 --> 00:05:54.995
Rajesh I have this big fat check that I am

00:05:54.995 --> 00:05:57.635
about to sign for a large enterprise

00:05:57.635 --> 00:05:58.435
software vendor

00:05:59.316 --> 00:06:01.956
Hundreds of millions of dollars I'm not

00:06:01.956 --> 00:06:04.036
sure if we should sign it Why

00:06:04.836 --> 00:06:05.236
One

00:06:06.116 --> 00:06:07.956
I don't know what all AI is going to

00:06:07.956 --> 00:06:08.516
change

00:06:09.752 --> 00:06:12.792
Second this vendor is telling everybody on

00:06:12.792 --> 00:06:15.032
Wall Street that they are getting twenty

00:06:15.032 --> 00:06:17.912
thirty percent efficiency because of AI

00:06:18.552 --> 00:06:20.552
but I'm not seeing my bill go down twenty

00:06:20.552 --> 00:06:21.192
thirty percent

00:06:22.472 --> 00:06:25.192
And lastly I don't even use everything

00:06:25.272 --> 00:06:27.032
that they're buying from them

00:06:27.983 --> 00:06:28.863
We use only a part

00:06:29.823 --> 00:06:31.423
So this is what I am thinking Rajesh She

00:06:31.423 --> 00:06:31.663
said

00:06:33.183 --> 00:06:35.663
Should I get a set of developers from my

00:06:35.663 --> 00:06:35.903
team

00:06:37.023 --> 00:06:39.503
and ask them to build parts of the

00:06:39.503 --> 00:06:40.303
software

00:06:41.200 --> 00:06:44.320
Using Claude Code or other you know coding

00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:47.600
tools and then use it and then instead of

00:06:47.600 --> 00:06:50.160
me maintaining it turn the whole thing to

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:51.360
open source

00:06:52.320 --> 00:06:55.520
This was in September even before we saw

00:06:55.520 --> 00:06:57.760
the market trash software stocks

00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:01.280
So CIOs are grappling with these questions

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:02.800
How will impact the future of IT

00:07:04.536 --> 00:07:06.376
So we looked deep into that and then what

00:07:06.376 --> 00:07:09.336
we realized is that there are a set of

00:07:09.336 --> 00:07:11.496
things that need to be considered This is

00:07:11.496 --> 00:07:14.296
not a trivial exercise We all know how

00:07:14.376 --> 00:07:16.376
hard transformation programs are that you

00:07:16.376 --> 00:07:16.776
work on

00:07:18.136 --> 00:07:20.456
So in this presentation we wanted to offer

00:07:20.456 --> 00:07:22.296
you three things that are the outcome of

00:07:22.296 --> 00:07:23.016
that research

00:07:24.418 --> 00:07:28.098
The first is what is the future state that

00:07:28.178 --> 00:07:31.298
you should aim for What is that North Star

00:07:32.098 --> 00:07:34.498
We developed a few models We call them

00:07:34.578 --> 00:07:36.818
archetypes to help you bring through that

00:07:38.805 --> 00:07:39.205
Second

00:07:40.005 --> 00:07:42.885
what is the level of reskilling or job

00:07:42.885 --> 00:07:44.725
changes you will have to consider for

00:07:44.725 --> 00:07:45.605
people in your team

00:07:46.890 --> 00:07:48.730
And it's not just deciding on the level of

00:07:48.730 --> 00:07:49.450
changes

00:07:50.410 --> 00:07:52.010
What is the right pace for you

00:07:53.050 --> 00:07:55.050
Some of you might want to be AI first and

00:07:55.050 --> 00:07:55.770
go all in

00:07:56.650 --> 00:07:58.250
but at the other extreme some of you want

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:00.330
to be really cautious That's

00:08:00.330 --> 00:08:02.010
understandable based on the nature of the

00:08:02.010 --> 00:08:02.570
industry

00:08:03.931 --> 00:08:06.171
And third we will look into the

00:08:06.171 --> 00:08:08.171
implication to the tech stack itself

00:08:09.691 --> 00:08:11.291
So these are the three areas that we are

00:08:11.291 --> 00:08:12.731
going to look into as part of this

00:08:12.731 --> 00:08:14.571
presentation and we have much more

00:08:14.571 --> 00:08:15.531
research on this

00:08:17.451 --> 00:08:21.051
So now to look into the future state model

00:08:22.142 --> 00:08:24.462
What we see is it's important to consider

00:08:24.542 --> 00:08:25.582
three different factors

00:08:26.462 --> 00:08:26.782
One

00:08:27.662 --> 00:08:28.382
supply itself

00:08:29.822 --> 00:08:33.582
Because of AIdriven efficiency we see that

00:08:33.742 --> 00:08:36.222
more can be done with the same number of

00:08:36.222 --> 00:08:37.262
people or less

00:08:38.858 --> 00:08:39.258
Second

00:08:40.058 --> 00:08:42.058
what is your business telling you about

00:08:42.218 --> 00:08:43.258
demand in the future

00:08:44.378 --> 00:08:47.098
Not just based on how business is today

00:08:47.818 --> 00:08:49.578
but what are their aspirations for

00:08:49.578 --> 00:08:51.338
business Will they be investing in new

00:08:51.338 --> 00:08:54.218
markets Will they want to increase margin

00:08:54.618 --> 00:08:57.258
improve customer service Based on that

00:08:57.418 --> 00:08:58.618
what is the trajectory

00:09:00.058 --> 00:09:02.138
And these two used to be somewhat standard

00:09:02.138 --> 00:09:03.738
when we match demand and supply

00:09:04.778 --> 00:09:08.458
But the third factor is very important now

00:09:09.498 --> 00:09:12.778
democratization the ability of business to

00:09:12.858 --> 00:09:15.418
build technology What is the appetite in

00:09:15.418 --> 00:09:16.218
your business

00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:20.000
So when you use these three factors and

00:09:20.080 --> 00:09:22.000
then determine what are the models that

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:26.000
are possible we find there are four key

00:09:26.160 --> 00:09:29.280
archetypes that are important for you to

00:09:29.280 --> 00:09:30.720
consider and we offer you to them

00:09:33.290 --> 00:09:35.690
So what you see on the left is the demand

00:09:35.690 --> 00:09:38.890
supply and then the democratization Notice

00:09:38.890 --> 00:09:41.210
supply has got two elements number of

00:09:41.210 --> 00:09:43.130
people and the units of work being

00:09:43.130 --> 00:09:45.370
delivered They are not exactly the same

00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:48.650
The belief is because of AI you can

00:09:48.650 --> 00:09:51.130
deliver more with the same number of

00:09:51.130 --> 00:09:53.370
people or less but how much more it

00:09:53.370 --> 00:09:54.170
depends on your appetite

00:09:55.770 --> 00:09:57.850
The first archetype is what we call lean

00:09:57.850 --> 00:09:58.010
IT

00:09:59.332 --> 00:09:59.812
Here

00:10:00.772 --> 00:10:02.292
the demand is more or less the same

00:10:03.572 --> 00:10:06.052
but the expectation is IT can be more

00:10:06.052 --> 00:10:08.852
efficient with AI and can the size of IT

00:10:08.852 --> 00:10:11.652
can go somewhat smaller than it is today

00:10:12.870 --> 00:10:14.710
There are organizations who to whom I

00:10:14.710 --> 00:10:18.470
presented this that clearly say Yes you

00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:21.670
know my CEO or my board expects me to be

00:10:21.910 --> 00:10:26.070
lean IT or We are owned by a private

00:10:26.070 --> 00:10:28.390
equity firm that is expecting us to

00:10:28.390 --> 00:10:29.190
proceed that way

00:10:31.173 --> 00:10:33.333
Some of you tell us that you are seeing

00:10:33.333 --> 00:10:34.373
demand increase

00:10:35.333 --> 00:10:38.293
but there is no appetite to increase

00:10:38.293 --> 00:10:39.253
headcount in IT

00:10:40.613 --> 00:10:43.093
Through AIdriven efficiencies you want to

00:10:43.093 --> 00:10:43.893
match the demand

00:10:45.093 --> 00:10:46.213
This is amplified IT

00:10:49.173 --> 00:10:51.573
Some of you tell us that you know we are

00:10:51.573 --> 00:10:52.853
seeing significant demand

00:10:53.897 --> 00:10:56.377
But there is no appetite to increase IT

00:10:56.377 --> 00:10:59.497
Yes we do want IT to deliver more

00:11:00.457 --> 00:11:02.697
but we expect some of the demand to be

00:11:02.697 --> 00:11:06.137
satisfied directly by business We call

00:11:06.137 --> 00:11:07.257
this democratized IT

00:11:10.037 --> 00:11:13.317
And some of you say that we are seeing

00:11:13.317 --> 00:11:15.637
significant potential for technology

00:11:15.717 --> 00:11:16.357
across

00:11:17.397 --> 00:11:20.277
We want to build more In fact technology

00:11:20.277 --> 00:11:23.557
is so critical we might reduce our buy

00:11:23.557 --> 00:11:26.677
solutions and build somewhat more using AI

00:11:26.677 --> 00:11:27.237
tools

00:11:28.116 --> 00:11:31.076
So we want business to become more adept

00:11:31.156 --> 00:11:33.636
in building technology but we also want to

00:11:33.716 --> 00:11:36.436
invest in IT to deliver more technology

00:11:37.316 --> 00:11:39.476
Because everybody builds we call it the

00:11:39.556 --> 00:11:40.596
dual builder IT

00:11:42.413 --> 00:11:43.453
So take a look at this

00:11:44.653 --> 00:11:46.413
In terms of these four archetypes

00:11:47.613 --> 00:11:48.813
this is not a progression

00:11:50.013 --> 00:11:52.413
It is not unnecessarily one has to go from

00:11:52.413 --> 00:11:53.133
one to the other

00:11:54.253 --> 00:11:56.413
There might be a couple of places where

00:11:56.653 --> 00:11:58.333
some might consider you know why we are

00:11:58.333 --> 00:12:00.413
amplified We want to go to democratize

00:12:00.653 --> 00:12:01.213
That's okay

00:12:02.093 --> 00:12:04.013
Some might say we are democratized We want

00:12:04.093 --> 00:12:05.773
to go to dual builder That's okay

00:12:06.573 --> 00:12:08.013
But it's not a natural progression

00:12:10.710 --> 00:12:13.190
Think about what do you think is the model

00:12:13.270 --> 00:12:13.670
that suits you

00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.110
and also think about what does your CEO

00:12:17.350 --> 00:12:19.910
think the model that is needed for your

00:12:19.910 --> 00:12:22.550
organization And how do you determine that

00:12:23.430 --> 00:12:24.790
There are two factors to keep in mind

00:12:25.990 --> 00:12:28.550
If the transformation that you expect to

00:12:28.550 --> 00:12:31.350
do because of AI is fundamentally only in

00:12:31.350 --> 00:12:32.070
technology

00:12:33.190 --> 00:12:34.470
these two models are fine

00:12:35.554 --> 00:12:38.354
But if the model has to address changes on

00:12:38.354 --> 00:12:39.474
the business side as well

00:12:40.754 --> 00:12:43.714
the other two modelsdemocratized and dual

00:12:43.794 --> 00:12:44.754
buildercome to the fore

00:12:47.954 --> 00:12:50.114
The other way to look at this also is

00:12:50.194 --> 00:12:52.754
depends on how vital is technology to your

00:12:52.754 --> 00:12:53.314
business

00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:55.874
Everybody says technology is important

00:12:56.034 --> 00:12:56.674
That's not the issue

00:12:58.192 --> 00:12:59.632
But in some places

00:13:00.592 --> 00:13:02.432
it's much much more important to be stable

00:13:03.072 --> 00:13:04.432
not risk unnecessarily

00:13:05.552 --> 00:13:07.312
Stability triumphs innovation in those

00:13:07.312 --> 00:13:10.592
places We tend to see lean and amplified

00:13:10.592 --> 00:13:10.992
IT

00:13:12.352 --> 00:13:14.272
And in the middle this is where we expect

00:13:14.352 --> 00:13:15.472
most of you to be

00:13:16.352 --> 00:13:19.552
It is you are investing in technology to

00:13:19.552 --> 00:13:21.152
make use of the opportunities

00:13:22.118 --> 00:13:24.438
Which is common but then there is a subset

00:13:24.438 --> 00:13:26.198
of you for whom technology is critical

00:13:26.678 --> 00:13:27.558
What do I mean by that

00:13:28.438 --> 00:13:29.637
In these companies

00:13:30.517 --> 00:13:32.998
if a competitor or a new entrant

00:13:32.998 --> 00:13:36.118
introduces a technologybased product and

00:13:36.118 --> 00:13:39.318
that can impact you or your business

